div.note:
2595 One consisting,U+0026c. “These words,” says Gabriel, “are indeed a two-edged sword against the heretics,
for one clause mortally wounds Nestorius who separates the Divine from the Human Nature—the other Eutyches,
who empties the human into the Divine.”

div.p:
The Injunction of your inimitable Honour is not barbaric, but Greek, or rather christian;
but as for the Armenian on whom you pride yourself so, he is a downright barbarian, and
far from our honour.
